description: Enemies that attack Tiny have a 20% chance of being stunned for 1.0 second and taking 100 damage. Affects enemies within 400 range of him. Procs after an attack impacts, and does not affect spell immune enemies.

language.displayName: +20 Finger of Death Damage Per Kill

description: Creates a larger circle of trees in a 300 AoE for 6 seconds. Ensnares enemies inside for 2 seconds, dealing 150 damage per second.

Alchemist throws a potion at an ally, applying a basic dispel and giving them 50 Attack Speed and 40 HP regen.

Lasts 10 seconds.
Rock spikes burst from the earth along a straight path. Enemy units are hurled into the air, then are stunned and take damage when they fall.
language.lore: The Demon Witch exercises his demonic covenant, opening a fissure from hell.
notes: The spikes move at 1600 / 1600 / 1600 / 1600 units per second.

description: Transforms an enemy unit into a harmless beast, with all special abilities disabled.
language.lore: Lion is compelled to share his transfiguration, twisting the essence of those who oppose him.
notes: Instantly destroys illusions.
The target will have a base movement speed of 120, but buffs granting maximum movement speed won't be disabled.

description: CHANNELED - Absorbs the magical energies of a target enemy unit by taking mana from it every second.
language.lore: Lesser magi are nothing more than a source of magical restoration for the Demon Witch.
notes: Instantly destroys illusions.

description: Rips at an enemy unit, trying to turn it inside-out. Deals massive damage and grows stronger with each life it consumes.
language.lore: Lion's disfigured hand is also the source of his greatest power, capable of flooding victims with malefic force.
notes: Finger of Death has a 0.25 delay before the damage is applied after the spell is cast, allowing certain abilities to avoid the damage.
Finger of Death only gains damage if the enemy hero dies within 3 seconds of being affected by Finger of Death.

description: Wraith King's form regroups after death, allowing him to resurrect when killed in battle. Upon death, enemy units in a 900 radius will be slowed.
language.lore: Conspirators against the Wraith King wonder why he never stays dead.
notes: Wraith King won't revive if he doesn't have enough mana.
If Wraith King has an Aegis and Reincarnation off cooldown, Reincarnation will trigger first.
Revives with full HP and Mana.
Credit for allies whose death was delayed will go to whoever struck the original killing blow.
Wraith Delay affects Wraith King's actual deaths, not Reincarnate deaths.

description: Sends a swarm of winged beasts to savage enemy units in front of Death Prophet.
language.lore: Krobelus' many trips to the grave gather a flock of the damned.
notes: Can hit units up to 1110 range away.

description: Witch Doctor focuses his magic to heal nearby allied units, costing Witch Doctor mana every second Voodoo restoration is active.
language.lore: Zharvakko's hocus pocus is not limited only to hexxing his opponents and is quite adept at curing ailments.
notes: Healing is done in 0.33 / 0.33 / 0.33 / 0.33 second intervals.
Can heal Spell Immune units.

description: Transforms a creep into three fragments of Enigma himself.  These eidolons are all under Enigma's control, and repeated successful attacks cause them to multiply.  When this happens, the eidolons have their health restored.
language.lore: Enigma is capable of drawing aspects of himself from other dimensions - the result is a trio of dark eidolons that hunt the corporeal plane.
notes: Converted enemy units will give gold bounty and experience.
Converted allied units will be denied.

description: Burns the Golem's nearby enemy units, with damage per second.
Templar Assassin becomes highly elusive, avoiding damage and gaining a bonus to her damage.  The damage and avoidance effects are separate, and have a limited number of instances.
language.lore: Manipulating her psionic veil, Lanaya bends nature's law to her will.
notes: Damage as HP Removal bypasses Refraction (it won't reduce the charges).
Only instances of 5 / 5 / 5 / 5 or more damage will trigger Refraction.
Refraction is visible to enemies.

description: Templar Assassin places mystical traps that invisibly monitor enemy movement. When sprung at her command, they exert a slowing influence of 30% in the area. Traps charge up to slow 60% after 4 seconds. Deals bonus damage when fully charged.
language.lore: Calling upon the reach of the Hidden Temple, none escape the eye of the Templar.
notes: Traps last indefinitely.
They have invisibility that fades in over 2.0 / 2.0 / 2.0 seconds, spell immunity, and 100 HP.
Traps have 400/400 vision range and don't prevent neutral camps from spawning.

description: Deals damage to the unit that kills the Necronomicon Warrior.
Reveals invisible units.
Mana burned per hit, a portion of which is dealt as damage.

Roshan possesses numerous protective abilities, including 55%% magic damage resistance, the ability to reduce damage from attacking illusions, and a scaling armor bonus that increases as time goes on.
Sprouts a ring of trees around a unit, trapping it in place, and providing vision in a 500 radius.
language.lore: Verdant overgrowth is a common ailment reported by Nature's Prophet's attackers.
notes: Sprout can be cast on any unit, or the ground.
Trees created by Sprout have the same interactions with abilities as regular trees.

description: Teleports to any point on the map.
language.lore: The Prophet keeps his sentinel over the forest, protecting it when in need.
notes: Mana and cooldown take effect when the cast is completed.  Nature's Prophet will not use any mana or waste the cooldown if the spell is interrupted while casting.
When the cast begins, an effect is created at the target location, which is visible to allies and enemies.

description: Converts an area of trees into Treants under the command of Nature's Prophet.
language.lore: Verodicia bestowed the Prophet with the ability to summon the Treant Guard, a mythical sentient army of the wild.
notes: Nature's Call can only create as many treants as there are trees in the target area.

description: Damaging energy bounces around the map, striking enemies close to the cast point that are in vision. Each enemy hit beyond the first adds damage. Enemies that die under this spell grant you bonus damage for 50 seconds.
language.lore: Nature's Prophet calls Verodicia's fury to strike down those who might ravage the wilderness.
notes: Wrath of Nature will not hit units out of vision.
Can be cast through the minimap; the nearest valid target will be selected.

description: Surrounds the target unit with a bristling shield that damages enemy units in an area around it.
language.lore: The Dark Seer slices holes into the 'Land Behind the Wall,' causing prismatic energy to seep forth.
notes: Deals small amounts of damage in 0.1 second intervals.
Doesn't damage the target it is cast on.
If cast on a unit that already has Ion Shell, the new Shell replaces the old one.

description: Instantly heals a friendly unit and damages all nearby enemy units.
language.lore: Priests of the Omniscience are adept at removing impurities from fellow warriors.

description: The Hellbear Smasher claps his massive hands together, creating a deafening blast. The blast damages nearby enemies and throws them off their footing.
The Drakken Sentinel has assumed a partially ethereal form, making him difficult to hit with attacks.
The Drakken Armorer moves about quickly, making him difficult to hit with attacks.
The Drakken Armorer is wholly devoted to his cause, increasing his tolerance for physical attacks. Nearby allies are similarly devoted to the Overseer and are able to withstand more blows.

Chen takes control of an enemy or neutral creep. If the persuaded creep's base health is naturally below the health minimum, its base health will be raised to the health minimum. Converted creeps will have increased movement speed and bonus damage.
Can be cast on converted creeps to teleport them to Chen. If cast on Chen, all units controlled by Chen will be teleported to him. Taking damage will dispel the buff.
language.lore: Although they may not be knights, Chen incorporates beasts into the Fold in the same way he himself was converted.
notes: Persuading a new creep above max unit count causes the oldest persuaded creep to die.
Can target Ancient Creeps when Chen has Aghanim's Scepter.
The health of creeps already under Chen's control does not update to the new level upon leveling Holy Persuasion further.
Fully restores the creep's mana upon converting.

description: Damage done to Spectre is reflected on her enemies, leaving her unharmed. The effect lessens with distance.
language.lore: A daunting task lies before enemies of Mercurial - killing a shadow with blade and magic.
notes: The reflected damage is not dealt to Spectre.
Illusions don't get this ability.
Damage is reflected before reductions, and is returned as the same damage type.

description: Places a frozen hex on an enemy unit that deals damage over time, but can be dispelled by moving away from the initial cast point.  If the enemy unit doesn't move outside of the given range, it will be stunned and frozen in place after 4 seconds.
language.lore: Kaldr's presence draws those around him into a frozen void, threatening to lock them in an icy prison for eternity.
notes: Deals damage every second.

description: Creates a vortex of icy energy that slows and increases magic damage done to enemies in its range.
language.lore: Frozen, caustic winds are at the whim of Kaldr, chilling the field of battle.
notes: Provides vision in a small area where it is placed.

description: Enhances Ancient Apparition's attack with increased range, heavy magic damage, and movement slow.
language.lore: The Ancient Apparition's eternal knowledge brings a frigid enchantment to his attacks.

description: Launches a tracer toward any location on the battlefield, which must be triggered again to mark the area to be blasted by a damaging explosion of hail. The further the tracer travels, the larger the explosion will be. Enemies caught in the explosion, or who touch the icy ball of hail as it travels, are Frostbitten, taking damage and prevented from regenerating or healing. If a Frostbitten unit's health drops below a certain percentage, they will instantly shatter.
language.lore: Ice storms from ages past flow through Kaldr's frosty limbs, crashing into the world and turning its inhabitants into monuments to his eternal power.
notes: Upon cast, this ability is replaced by Release, used to stop the tracer on the target area.
The area of effect is 275 + 50.0*TimeTraveled, capped at 1000. The freeze area along the path is 275.
Kill will be granted to the source of the damage that triggers the shatter.
The shatter effect doesn't work on illusions.
The HP Freeze prevents most kinds of healing, including the fountain, except Sunder, Time Lapse and Supernova.

description: Releases the ice blast to explode at the tracer's current location.
Structure takes reduced damage, and quickly regenerates any damage taken while no enemy creeps are nearby.
Structure takes reduced damage, and quickly regenerates any damage taken while no enemy creeps are nearby.

Alchemist brews up an unstable concoction that he can throw at an enemy hero, to stun and deal damage in an area around the explosion. The longer the concoction brews, the more damage it deals and the longer the stun. After 5.0 seconds, the brew reaches its maximum damage and stun time. However, after 5.5 seconds, the concoction will explode on Alchemist himself if not thrown.
language.lore: A silver lining to the failure of turning a mountain into gold, this volatile solution has destructive potential.
notes: While brewing, this ability is replaced by Unstable Concoction Throw.  Alchemist can move and act normally while brewing.
A timer above Alchemist's head will indicate the remaining brew time. This timer is visible to enemies.
You can deny yourself with this skill.
Unstable Concoction cannot be disjointed.
Once thrown, Unstable Concoction stops brewing.

description: Throw it before it blows up!
Burns nearby enemy units.
Banishes the targeted unit from the battlefield for a short duration.  Upon returning, two illusions of the banished unit are created under Shadow Demon's control.
language.lore: The pain of deception comes not while it happens, but when it is revealed.

description: Visage gathers charges of soul essence each time nearby heroes take more than 100 damage. When the essence is released, it deals base damage as well as damage for each gathered soul charge.
language.lore: The collected souls of the dead reach out to bring another into their fold.
notes: Charges are only gained for damage greater than 2.0 and less than 3000.0 that is dealt by a player or Roshan. Self-damage or Soul Assumption damage isn't counted.
Soul Assumption cannot be disjointed.

description: Tethers Io to an allied unit, granting bonus movement speed to both. When Io restores health or mana, tethered units target gains a larger portion of that amount. The tether breaks when the allied unit moves too far away, or Io cancels the tether.
language.lore: The benevolent touch of Io brings strength from between the planes.
notes: If you try to tether a unit that is 700 distance or further away from Io, he will latch on and pull himself closer to the tethered unit (to a distance of 300).
The tethered unit will heal faster and will heal even if Io is at full health.
Io's movement speed matches the tethered unit's.

description: Summon five particle spirits that dance in a circle around Io. If a particle collides with an enemy hero, it explodes, damaging all enemy units in an area around it.  Creeps take minor damage from touching a particle spirit, but do not cause them to explode.  When its duration ends, any remaining Spirits explode.
language.lore: Io twists the particles of the universe with its unimaginable capabilities.
notes: After summoning, Io can call the spirits in and out.

description: Io gains bonus attack speed, spell amplification, and HP Regen based on max health.  If Io is Tethered to an ally, that unit also gains the bonuses.
language.lore: Drawing on the energy of matter from all worlds, Io begins the unravelling of time.

description: Teleports Io and any tethered ally to any location. After the spell expires Io and any tethered ally will return to their original location. Double-click to teleport to your team's base fountain.
language.lore: Io is the embodiment of the mystery of the universe.
notes: Enemies receive a visual indicator in the world and on the minimap of the target location during the cast delay.
If Io is disabled during the cast delay, Relocate is cancelled.
If an allied hero is Tethered, that hero will teleported along with you. You can break the tether at any time to prevent that hero from teleporting with you.

description: Break the link to the tethered unit.
Sends the spirits closer to you. Can be toggled on and off.
Sends the spirits farther away from you. Can be toggled on and off.

Turns the enemies' numbers against them, dealing damage and granting you bonus movement speed per unit or per hero.  Deals bonus damage to illusions and summoned units as a percent of their current health.
language.lore: The archers of Stonehall are ready at Tresdin's command.

description: Removes debuffs and disables from the target friendly unit, and grants bonus attack speed and health regen for a short time.
DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
language.lore: The rallying horn of the Bronze Legion is able to inspire any heart.

description: When attacked, Legion Commander has a chance to immediately counterattack with bonus lifesteal.
language.lore: Tresdin knows that an enemy's most vulnerable moment often follows their fiercest stroke.

description: Legion Commander and the target enemy hero are forced to attack each other for a short duration.  Neither hero can use items or abilities.  If either hero dies during the duration, the hero winning the Duel gains permanent bonus damage.
language.lore: To face a soldier of Stonehall in single combat is a challenge few can resist.
notes: Duels will end if the units are pushed 2000 units apart.
Winning a Duel automatically casts Press the Attack on yourself.

description: Terrorblade brings forth an invulnerable dark reflection of all enemy heroes in a target area. Affected enemy heroes are slowed and attacked by their reflection.
language.lore: In the fractal prison of Foulfell, Terrorblade learned the truth of this old tale: you are your own worst enemy.  Now it is a lesson he teaches others.
notes: Reflections are untargetable, invulnerable illusions, that will be destroyed if the slow debuff is removed.
Reflections can only attack their source.

description: Faceless Void traps all nearby enemies in a time dilation field for 8 / 10 / 12 / 14 seconds, extending their cooldowns and slowing their movement and attack speed by 10% for each cooldown extended.
language.lore: For those facing off against Darkterror, each moment seems to stretch into eternity.
notes: Does not affect item cooldowns.

description: Automatically targets additional enemy units with a mana pool within 400 distance around the original target.
While tethered to a friendly Hero, each time that Hero attacks, Io will attack the same target automatically.
While tethered to a friendly Hero, that Hero gains its Aghanim's Scepter ability upgrades for the duration.
Summons Ignis Fatuus at the targeted area. Alternates on and off, drawing enemies closer with its mesmerising flicker.
language.lore: Though he would not claim to 'know' them, Ezalor holds an uncanny influence over many powerful creatures always willing to come to his aid.
